----------------------------------------------------------------------
Why two licenses?
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Hardware and software have different reuse and liability concerns. CERN-OHL-P
is purpose-built for hardware documentation and clearly defines terms like
"Product" and "Documentation"; MIT is the most frictionless choice for the
code, so anyone can drop the detector or consensus engine into their own
stack with zero ceremony. See docs/licensing.md for the full rationale.
